doc.previous: The border states California Arizona New Mexico and Texas all have large Hispanic populations and the many Spanish place names attest to their history as former Spanish and Mexican territories Other southwestern states such as Colorado Utah and Nevada have large Hispanic populations as well with many names places also attest to the history of former Mexican territories Mexican Americans have also had a growing population in Northwestern states of Oregon and Washington as well as the southern state of Oklahoma
doc.after: Alaska the northernmost state in the Union is a vast land of few people many of them native and of great stretches of wilderness protected in national parks and wildlife refuges Hawaii s location makes it a major gateway between the U S and Asia as well as a center for tourism
